FBIS4-6240 "dreas075_c_94010" FBIS-EAS-94-075 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 North Korea KCNA Cites ROK Radio on Greenpeace Rally KCNA Cites ROK Radio on Greenpeace Rally SK1904053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 19 Apr 94 SK1904053994 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- Greenpeace, the international organisation of environmental movement, urged the puppet authorities of South Korea to stop the construction project of the atomic power station now underway, according to a radio report from Seoul. Some 20 members of the organisation raised this demand at an anti-nuke rally they held in Samchok on April 14 with about 1,000 members of environmental protection and anti-nuke organisations of South Korea. Sounding a warning against the danger of radioactive leakage from the South Korean atomic power station, Greenpeace is strongly demanding a stop to its construction project, said the radio.
